5:
People are flies that drop dead in
the light.
8:
I am a spider. I spin webs to cocoon
my prey.
11:
We act according to our natures, no
more complicated than water
flowing down a stream.
14:
Logic dictates that there is nothing
more to expect from the world.
31:
Not the behavior of a sane master,
for certain. I was right to keep them
a secret from the imperial court.
34:
This will need to be dealt with. Let us
be off.
41:
So what is the plan for the
foreseeable future?
43:
We've avoided outright conflict
these past seven days. But the
whole situation is a powder keg
waiting to go off still.
58: Can you help us do something else?
67: Want to do things fairly again?
71:
If we push the Palpebrans into a
corner, they'll never forgive us.
73:
Besides, doing something once
means setting a precedent.
76:
So you've set the precedent for
dragging cities here on a whim. But
you'd rather not add threats to that
precedent.
79:
Yeah, I'd like to keep negotiations
civil.
83:
Then we'll need time for tempers to
cool and assessments to be made.
86:
This is the perfect time to ensnare
the hasty, create delays, and deflect
any suspicion all the while.
88:
You're good at those things, aren't
you? Though you'll have to work
hard if you want to be overlooked.
92:
Oh? I wouldn't bother with that.
You're welcome to confront me
directly if you wish.
96:
Er, you guys can verbally spar all
you want, but... don't go too far, okay?
100:
Relax. I promise I'll keep things
subtle, like I always do.
115:
But of course. You look bored out of
your mind.
117:
Though I suppose you were already
bored long before you came here.
121:
You and your little pranks. I can
never take you seriously.
130:
...Though if you truly believe that,
perhaps you understand.
132:
People are people. No matter what
twists and turns life takes, we all end
up in the same place.
134:
Isn't this boredom just another
constant of life?
139: Hmm. So she hasn't noticed yet.
146:
Spread confusion for now. If you
sense panic building, put a stop to it
and spread different information.
149:
But don't say anything that directly
contradicts the truth. That's the only
request our allies had.
153: Now be on your way. Scatter!
159:
I believe you have a task of your
own.
162:
I would like to be stationed in that
city too.
171: ...Well, now. Interested in me, are you?
173:
No, not like that. I can't explain why...
because even I don't know the
reason.
184:
Very well. Do whatever you like. Have
at it.
193:
...Am I excited... for the possibility of
change?
196:
Perhaps I'm the one who's been
ensnared in their web.
